max_value = df.groupby('Species')['PetalLengthCm'].mean().max()

# Calculating Upper fence and lower Fence
Q1 = df['SepalLengthCm'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['SepalLengthCm'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
lower_fence = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_fence = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
print("Lower Fence:", lower_fence)
print("Upper Fence:", upper_fence)

Computing the z-score for each value in the 'PetalWidthCm' column and identifying any outliers



        

      


      

        
        
↳ 0 cells hidden

      

      

    

      

        

          
          

            
          

        

      
from scipy import stats
zscores = stats.zscore(df['PetalWidthCm'])
z_scores_list = list(zscores)
outliers = []
for i in range(len(z_scores_list)):
    if abs(z_scores_list[i]) > 3:
        outliers.append(z_scores_list[i])
print(len(outliers))
if len(outliers) > 0:
    print("Outliers:", outliers)
else:
    print("No outliers found.")

    
 
 

        

          

          

            
 
0
No outliers found.
